# Cursor Rules for Gradiently Site

## CSS and Styling Rules

**CRITICAL: Do not write any CSS code.**

- We have tooling for CSS processing (Tailwind CSS)
- Only use Tailwind utility classes in HTML files
- Do not create or modify CSS files directly
- Do not write custom CSS rules or styles
- Do not use `<style>` tags in HTML

## HTML Guidelines

- Use only Tailwind utility classes for styling
- Keep HTML semantic and clean
- Use proper Tailwind responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- Leverage Tailwind's built-in utilities for spacing, colors, typography, etc.

## File Structure

- HTML files: Use Tailwind classes only
- CSS files: Managed by build tooling, do not edit
- Configuration: Update Tailwind config if needed for custom utilities

## Examples

✅ Good:
```html
<div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-pink-500 p-8 rounded-lg">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white">Title</h1>
</div>
```

❌ Bad:
```html
<div style="background: linear-gradient(...)">
  <h1 style="font-size: 2rem; color: white;">Title</h1>
</div>
```

❌ Bad:
```css
.custom-gradient {
  background: linear-gradient(...);
}
```

## Build Process

- CSS is processed by Tailwind CLI
- Custom utilities should be added to Tailwind config
- Use `@apply` directive in Tailwind config for custom components if needed
- Never write raw CSS in project files
